{"type":"card","data":{"approach":"Converting this to an array of [F,F,FT,T] is a creativity problem. You have to be creative. Write down the problem and array numbers with index. Check if it creates any pattern, check if you create a certain feasible function condition then it creates a pattern.\nImmediate task: turn “find the peak” into “find the first index where some condition becomes true.”\nGuiding question: what local comparison tells you whether you’re on the increasing side or the decreasing side?\n\nA practical checklist:\n\nNotice the structure words: “increases then decreases”, “mountain”, “single peak”.\nThat screams: there’s a single turning point (a boundary).","difficulty":5.71,"due":1783663895108,"elapsed_days":0,"historyLog":[1783269215240,1783269215240,1783308236111,1783577495108],"id":"1783269215240","lapses":0,"lastRating":4,"reps":3,"scheduled_days":1,"spaceComplexity":"","stability":0.6,"state":2,"tags":["Binary Search"],"textRead":"","timeComplexity":"","u":1}}
